**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Secrets are embedded in source and will leak via Git history, logs, and builds.
- A single compromise of the repository or CI artifacts exposes all environments.
- Static IV and long-lived keys make past and future encrypted data decryptable forever if keys leak.

**SECURE VERSION**:

